    "description": "Taiyo Bussan Kaisha,Ltd. engages in trading food products in Japan. It operates through four segments: Food Division, Agricultural Products Division, China Development Division, and Lifestyle Division. The company offers beef, lamb, chicken, other livestock products, as well as seafood and processed seafood products, vegetables and fruits, processed foods, and frozen food ingredients. It also trades in soy for miso, bean sprouts, tofu, soybean flour, natto, animal feed; soba for brown buckwheat and hulled buckwheat kernels; mung beans for bean sprouts and food; black mappe for bean sprouts; defatted soybeans for brewing for soy sauce; miscellaneous grains; and others, including peanuts, various feeds, apple juice, and boiled mushrooms. In addition, the company offers commercial vehicles, vehicle engines, other vehicle parts, and special-purpose vehicles; water treatment facilities; cosmetics, alcoholic beverages, and supplements; various machines and parts, other lifestyle-related products, and various brand-name products; and chemical industry raw materials, cosmetic raw materials, and health food raw materials. Taiyo Bussan Kaisha,Ltd. was founded in 1936 and is headquartered in Shinjuku, Japan."
